    Several companies offer Laravel web development services. Some highly-rated options include Webkul, WPWeb Infotech, Hidden Brains, iGex Solutions, and Innowise. These companies offer expertise in building scalable, secure, and high-performance web applications using the Laravel framework. 
    Here's a more detailed look at some of these companies:
    • Webkul:
      Webkul is a leading Laravel Development Company with experience in eCommerce and software development, according to their website. They offer a range of services, including custom Laravel development, and are known for their support team and focus on delivering quality solutions. 
    • WPWeb Infotech:
      WPWeb Infotech is a trusted Laravel development company that builds scalable and secure web applications. They offer dedicated Laravel developers for hire and have expertise across various industries. 
    • Hidden Brains:
      Hidden Brains specializes in developing high-performance Laravel applications. They leverage the advantages of the Laravel framework to create custom web solutions. 
    • iGex Solutions:
      iGex Solutions is a custom Laravel development company offering a range of web development services, including website design and SEO. They pride themselves on providing 100% client-oriented solutions and free 30-day support. 
    • Innowise:
      Innowise provides top-tier Laravel web development services, building applications from scratch or joining ongoing projects. They focus on leveraging the benefits of Laravel, such as outstanding security and performance.

      Which company owns Laravel?
      Laravel was created in June 2011 by Taylor Otwell. It is a free and open-source PHP framework allowing you to create websites and web apps using its huge libraries so you don't have to write code from scratch. What this means is that Laravel isn't owned by any entity.
